27/08/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- UN High Commissioner for Refugees Antonio Guterres wrapped up a two-day visit to BiH on Wednesday (August 26th), after meeting with entity officials of the Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina and Republika Srpska (RS).
After talks with RS Prime Minister Milorad Dodik in Banja Luka, Guterres urged BiH, Croatia and Serbia to work together to resolve refugees' return issues.
He also called on Bosnian Serb authorities to work harder to resolve the situation of the remaining 117,000 displaced people within the country.
During a stop in Srebrenica, Guterres paid tribute to massacre victims at the Potocari Memorial Centre.
Guterres is in Belgrade on Thursday to discuss the refugee situation in Serbia and the region as a whole.
(Beta - 27/08/09;
RTRS, Fena, Tanjug - 26/08/09)
